===Multidimensional version===
As with the multidimensional central limit theorem, there is a multidimensional version of the Berry–Esseen theorem.

:Let formula_24 be independent formula_25-valued random vectors each having mean zero. Write formula_26 and assume formula_27 is invertible. Let formula_28 be a formula_29-dimensional Gaussian with the same mean and covariance matrix as formula_30. Then for all convex sets formula_31,
